Vladimir Putin would "quite likely be poisoned" if he were to be assassinated, a former KGB spy has said. Yuri Shvets, 71, said the Russian president "fears for his life" over fears of a "meat grinder" power struggle in his inner circle. As a result, Putin has isolated himself over his fears, travelling in a specially armoured train to avoid air travel and staying in locations where flights are "significantly limited". But speaking on any assassination attempts, Mr Shvets said: “Quite likely he will be poisoned. This is the easiest way.” FOLLOW BELOW FOR UPDATES...